title: Merge pull request #7 from pdpiech/master
message:
Merge pull request #7 from pdpiech/master

Tweak ListView for MapFragment, fix various bugs

title: Tweak ListView for MapFragment, fix various bugs
message:
Tweak ListView for MapFragment, fix various bugs

MainActivity:
- Add check for YouTube being installed before opening "Videos"
- Add Google Play Services check; display message if not installed

MapFragment:
- Consistent row height in ListView
- Migrate to using ArrayAdapter instead of BaseAdapter
- Remove need to extend BaseAdapter class; auto-handling; less code
- Fix bug where returning to ListView from GoogleMap duplicated list
- Move database parsing code into separate method; use new database file
- Add check for Google Play Services; prevent app crash if not installed

map_fragment.xml:
- edit in order to work with ArrayAdapter auto-handling

map_list_item.xml:
- edit in order to work with ArrayAdapter auto-handling

ViewMapFragment:
- Implement onDeleteView method to prevent duplicate IDs error
- Move logic over from MapListAdapter class
- Remove debugging code

MapLocation:
- Implement toString method required for ArrayAdapter to function
properly

MapListAdapter:
- Entirely comment out; no longer needed by MapFragment
- Code may be useful for implementation of TV Guide feature

AthleticsFragment:
- Close RSS reader variable after use; fix resource leak warning

WeatherFragment:
- Comment out unused variables and removed unused imports
- Variables will prove useful for adding graphics back later

strings.xml:
- Change app name: "RPI Mobile" (with a space)
- Remove unused values

content.db:
- change name from "map_locations.db"
- Now contains new table for future TV Guide implementation with sample
entry

title: Version 0.8 - Campus Map
message:
Version 0.8 - Campus Map

- The package name has been changed back to rpi.edu.rpimobile. This is
the package name on the play store and can't be changed. It is incorrect
and should technically be edu.rpi.rpimobile, but the application needs
to be re-released for the package name to change and everyone must
download a new app.
- The twitter4j library has been updated to use ssl, which is now
required by twitter.
- maps API key has been updated to continue using the same keystore.
